th Kim Jun-hyun and [[Lee Kyu-han]]\n|}\n\n===Musical theatre===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2012\u20132013\n| ''[[Catch Me If You Can (musical)|Catch Me If You Can]]''\n| Brenda Strong \n|rowspan=2| Lead Role\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Singin' in the Rain (musical)|Singin' in the Rain]]''\n| Kathy Selden \n|-\n| 2016\u20132017\n| ''Cafe-in ~Mr Sommelier Miss Barista''\n|\n| Lead Role, Japanese musical\n|}\n\n===Radio show===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2008\n| Melon Chunji Radio\n| Co-DJ with [[Super Junior]]'s [[Lee Sung-min (singer)|Sungmin]]\n|-\n| 2014\u20132015\n| [[HLKV-FM|MBC FM4U]]'s [[:ko:FM \ub370\uc774\ud2b8|Sunny's FM Date]] \n| Solo DJ\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{{Main|List of awards and nominations received by Girls' Generation}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Awards\n! Category\n! Work\n! Result\n! Ref.\n|-\n| 2010\n|[[Mnet 20's Choice Awards]]\n|Hot Female Multitainer\n|\n| rowspan=\"3\" {{Nominated}}\n| \n|-\n| 2012\n| The 6th Musical Awards\n| rowspan=\"2\" | Best New Actress\n| rowspan=\"2\" | ''[[Catch Me If You Can (musical)|Catch Me If You Can]]''\n|\n|-\n| 2013\n| The 19th Korean Musical Awards\n|\n|-\n| 2014 \n| [[MBC Entertainment Awards]]\n| Rookie Radio DJ Award \n| ''Sunny's FM Date''\n| {{won}}\n|<ref name=radioaward/>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|35em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n<!--per [[WP:EL]], ONE official website is allowed. Pick one and that's it. This is not an SNS directory.-->\n* {{IMDb person|id=4227258}}\n\n{{Girls' Generation}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sunny}}\n[[Category:1989 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Orange County, California]]\n[[Category:American dance musicians]]\n[[Category:American expatriates in South Korea]]\n[[Category:American female pop singers]]\n[[Category:American pop singers]]\n[[Category:American musicians of Korean descent]]\n[[Category:American women of Korean descent]]\n[[Category:American television hosts]]\n[[Category:English-language singers from South Korea]]\n[[Category:Girls' Generation members]]\n[[Category:Japanese-language singers of South Korea]]\n[[Category:Mandarin-language singers of South Korea]]\n[[Category:South Korean female idols]]\n[[Category:Radio personalities from California]]\n[[Category:21st-century American singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century American women singers]]\n[[Category:Women television presenters]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Korean-American singer}}\n{{other people||Sunny (disambiguation){{!}}Sunny}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2019}}\n{{Korean name|Lee}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name             = Sunny\n| image            = File:Sunny at Budweiser Project B Party on April 2018 01.png\n| image_size       = \n| caption          = Sunny in April 2018\n| native_name      = \uc774\uc21c\uaddc\n| native_name_lang = ko\n| birth_name       = Susan Soonkyu Lee<ref name=\"birth name1\">{{cite web |title=The Birth of Susan Soonkyu Lee |url=https://www.californiabirthindex.org/birth/susan_soonkyu_lee_born_1989_19290280 |website=[[California Birth Index]] |accessdate=December 16, 2018 |language=English}}</ref>\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1989|5|15}}\n| birth_place      = [[Orange County, California]], U.S.\n| other_names      = Lee Soon-gyu<ref name=r1>{{cite web |url = http://sh.piao.com.cn/view/images/shanghai/smt/querenhan.html |title = SM Town Live '10 World Tour in Shanghai \"Artistes Confirmation\"(LEE SOONGYU) | work= sh.piao.com.cn (\u4e2d\u570b\u7968\u52d9\u5728\u7dab) |language = Chinese |accessdate = January 8, 2015 }}</ref>\n| occupation       = {{hlist|Singer|entertainer}}\n| relatives        = [[Lee Soo-man]] (uncle)\n| module           = {{Infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n| background       = solo_singer\n| instrument       = Vocals\n| years_active     = 2007\u2013present\n| label            = [[SM Entertainment|SM]]\n| associated_acts  = {{hlist|[[Girls' Generation]]|[[Oh!GG|Girls' Generation-Oh!GG]]|[[SM Town]]}}\n}}\n}}\n{{Infobox Korean name\n| title       = [[Korean name]]\n| hangul      = {{linktext|\uc774|\uc21c|\uaddc}}\n| hanja       = {{linktext|\u674e|\u7d14|\u63c6}}\n| rr          = I Sun-gyu\n| mr          = I Sun-kyu\n| hangulstage = {{linktext|\uc368\ub2c8}}\n| rrstage     = Sseoni\n| mrstage     = Ss\u014fni\n}}\n'''Lee Soon-gyu'''<ref name=\"r1\" /> (born May 15, 1989), known professionally as '''Sunny''', is an American singer and entertainer based in South Korea. She debuted as a member of girl group [[Girls' Generation]] (and later its subgroup [[Oh!GG|Girls' Generation-Oh!GG]]) in August 2007, which went on to become one of the best-selling artists in South Korea and one of South Korea's most popular girl groups worldwide. Apart from her group's activities, Sunny has participated in numerous side projects including original soundtracks, television variety shows, musical acting and radio hosting.\n\n==Life and career==\n===1989\u20132007: Early life and career beginnings===\nSunny was born on May 15, 1989, in [[Orange County, California|Orange County]], California.<ref name=\"past and present\"/> Her family consists of her parents and two older sisters who are ten and fifteen years older than her. She and her sisters share the same birthday.<ref>{{cite web |script-title=ko:\uc18c\ub140\uc2dc\ub300 \uc368\ub2c8\uc5d0\uac8c 5\uc6d415\uc77c\uc774\ub780\u2026\ud655\ub960 13\ub9cc\ubd84\uc758 1|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=003&aid=0003676070|publisher=[[Naver]]|date=February 6, 2011|language=Korean}}</ref> Her father, Lee Soo-young, was also known to be the elder brother of [[SM Entertainment]] founder [[Lee Soo-man]]. While Sunny was still an infant, her family moved to [[Kuwait]], then moved again shortly after to [[South Korea]], during the time of the [[Gulf War]]. As a result of her brief war experience, Sunny grew up being scared of loud noises. She was influenced to become a singer by her father, who was in a college band. In 1998, Sunny joined SM Entertainment and became a trainee for five years. She transferred to Starworld agency, where her father worked as a manager, and was to debut in a duo group called Sugar. The group, however, never came to fruition. In early 2007, singer [[Iconiq|Ayumi Lee]] convinced Sunny to rejoin SM Entertainment. She continued her training there and made her official debut as a member of [[Girls' Generation]] in August 2007.<ref>{{cite web |script-title=ko:Invincible Youth \uccad\ucd98\ubd88\ud328 - Ep.15 : Lettuce patch planting, Mushroom cultivating|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=k-z2EuzMlaM|website=[[KBS World (TV channel)|KBS World]] on YouTube|publisher=Google Inc|accessdate=March 31, 2016|time=53:08|format=Video upload|date=July 29, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.newsen.com/news_view.php?uid=200903150049281001 |script-title=ko:\uc368\ub2c8 \"\ud0dc\uc5b4\ub098\uc790\ub9c8\uc790 \uac78\ud504\uc804 \ud53c\ub09c\ubbfc \uc0dd\ud65c\ud588\ub2e4\" \uae5c\uc9dd \uace0\ubc31|publisher=Newsen|date=March 15, 2009|language=korean|accessdate=April 3, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |script-title=ko:Talk 1, \ud1a0\ud06c, Lalala 20090625|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=P82sC6X7vQc|website=[[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]] on YouTube|publisher=Google Inc|accessdate=April 3, 2016|time=3:20|format=Video upload|date=June 3, 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"past and present\">{{Cite news|title=[Past And Present] Small But Cutest Girl, Sunny |last=Ahn|first=Woorim|work=BNT News|date=November 17, 2014|accessdate=July 11, 2015|url=http://www.bntnews.co.uk/app/news.php?nid=14820}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?idxno=2007113015350222567&nvr=|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110904123255/http://www.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?idxno=2007113015350222567&nvr= |script-title=ko:\uc18c\ub140\uc2dc\ub300 \uc368\ub2c8 SM \uc774\uc218\ub9cc \uce5c\uc870\uce74 '\uc288\uac00 \ud6c4\uc18d \uadf8\ub8f9 \uba64\ubc84 \ub420 \ubed4'|archivedate=September 4, 2011|website=[[Korea Economic Daily]]|date=November 30, 2007|accessdate=March 31, 2016|language=korean}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=076&aid=0000084242 |script-title=ko:\uc18c\ub140\uc2dc\ub300 \uc368\ub2c8, '\uc74c\uc545\uac00 \uc9d1\uc548' \uc774\uc218\ub9cc \uce5c\uc870\uce74 \ud654\uc81c|date=December 3, 2007|publisher=[[The Chosun Ilbo]]|language=korean|accessdate=March 31, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=003&aid=0003676070 |script-title=ko:\uc18c\ub140\uc2dc\ub300 \uc368\ub2c8\uc5d0\uac8c 5\uc6d415\uc77c\uc774\ub780\u2026\ud655\ub960 13\ub9cc\ubd84\uc758 1|date=February 6, 2011|accessdate=March 31, 2016|publisher=Newsis|language=korean}}</ref> The group gained significant popularity with the release of their hit single \"[[Gee (Girls' Generation song)|Gee]]\" in 2009.<ref>{{cite news|first=Do-yeun|last=Kim|url=http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/art/2011/11/135_97862.html|title=Girls' Generation featured on Yale School of Art website|date=November 2, 2011|accessdate=February 28, 2015|publisher=Korea Times}}</ref>\n\n===2008\u2013present: Solo activities===\n\nAside from Girls' Generation's activities, Sunny has participated in a number of side-projects. In early 2008, Sunny worked as a co-host of the Melon Chunji Radio with [[Super Junior]]'s [[Sungmin]].<ref>{{cite web |script-title=ko:Talk 2, \ud1a0\ud06c, Lalala 20090625|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OkF8ZDW-Y4k|website=[[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]] on YouTube|publisher=Google Inc|accessdate=April 3, 2016|time=2:15|format=Video upload|date=June 3, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.newsen.com/news_view.php?uid=200806030819421002 |script-title=ko:\u2018\uba85\ud488\ub77c\uc774\ube0c' \uc368\ub4dc\ucf54\uc2a4\ud2b8 \ubc29\uc1a1 \uc911 \ub77c\uc774\ube0c \uc74c\uc6d0 \uc694\uccad \ubd07\ubb3c|publisher=Newsen|date=June 3, 2008|accessdate=April 3, 2016|language=korean}}</ref> In August 2008, she contributed a solo song, \"You Don't Know About Love\" for the [[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]]'s drama ''[[Working Mom (TV series)|Working Mom]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.yesasia.com/us/working-mom-ost-sbs-tv-drama/1011774336-0-0-0-en/info.html|title=YesAsia's ''Working Mom'' OST|publisher=[[YesAsia]]|date=August 28, 2008|accessdate=April 2, 2016}}</ref> In 2009, Sunny released two songs\u2014a solo track \"Finally Now\" for the [[interactive movie]] ''[[Story of Wine]]'' and a duet \"It's Love\" for the [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]]'s drama ''Heading to the Ground'', with Girls' Generation's member [[Kim Tae-yeon|Taeyeon]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://osen.mt.co.kr/article/G0903050028 |script-title=ko:\ub178\ubbfc\uc6b0, \uc18c\uc2dc \uc368\ub2c8\uc640 \ud568\uaed8\ud55c \ubc1c\ub77c\ub4dc \uacf5\uac1c|language=Korean|publisher=Osen|date=March 5, 2009|accessdate=April 2, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?idxno=2009092415432495225 |script-title=ko:'\ub9e8\ub545\uc5d0 \ud5e4\ub529' OST \ud0dc\uc5f0-\uc368\ub2c8 '\uc0ac\ub791\uc778\uac78\uc694' \uc778\uae30 \uae09\uc0c1\uc2b9|language=Korean|publisher=Asia Economic|date=September 24, 2009|accessdate=April 2, 2016}}</ref> During 2009 and 2010, Sunny was a co-host for [[SBS MTV|MTV Korea]] television music program ''The M'' with [[SS501]]'s [[Kim Hyung-jun]] and [[2AM (band)|2AM]]'s [[Im Seulong]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://star.mt.co.kr/view/stview.php?no=2009040712140695357&type=1&outlink=1 |script-title=ko:'\uc9c0' \ud65c\ub3d9\ub9c8\uac10 \uc18c\ub140\uc2dc\ub300, \"\uc694\uc998 \uc774\ub807\uac8c \uc9c0\ub0b4\uc694~\"|date=April 9, 2009|publisher=StarNews|accessdate=April 2, 2016|language=Korean}}</ref> She also joined the [[KBS2]]'s variety show ''[[Invincible Youth]]'' along with Girls' Generation member [[Kwon Yuri|Yuri]]. The reality program narrated a journey of a group of South Korean celebrities who were brought together to work and experience the agricultural and rural life.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.newsen.com/news_view.php?uid=201005141851301002|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141007163925/http://www.newsen.com/news_view.php?uid=201005141851301002 |script-title=ko:\u2018\ud558\ucc28\uc124 \ub05d\ub0b4 \uc0ac\uc2e4\ub85c..' \uc720\ub9ac-\uc368\ub2c8-\ud604\uc544 19\uc77c '\uccad\ucd98\ubd88\ud328' \ub9c8\uc9c0\ub9c9 \ub179\ud654|publisher=Newsen|date=May 14, 2010|archivedate=October 7, 2014|language=korean}}</ref> In March 2010, Sunny recorded \"Your Doll\" for the SBS's drama ''[[Oh! My Lady]]'' soundtrack\u2014it became her first song to enter the [[Gaon Digital Chart]], at number 88.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://osen.mt.co.kr/article/G1003220039 |script-title=ko:\uc18c\uc2dc \uc368\ub2c8, '\uc624 \ub9c8\uc774 \ub808\uc774\ub514' OST \uba54\uc778 \ud0c0\uc774\ud2c0 \ubd88\ub7ec|publisher=Osen|date=2010|accessdate=April 2, 2016|language=Korean}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=ALL&targetTime=14&hitYear=2010&termGbn=week|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303170443/http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=ALL&targetTime=14&hitYear=2010&termGbn=week|title=Gaon Digital Chart - March 21\u201427, 2010 chart|publisher=[[Gaon Digital Chart]] (Korea Music Content Industry Association)|date=March 2010|archivedate=March 3, 2016|language=korean}}</ref> During 2011 and 2012, she continued on with her participation in KBS2's [[Invincible Youth 2]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://star.mt.co.kr/foreign/starViewEng.html?no=2012070717155474923|title=SNSD's Suuny leaves Invincible Youth 2|publisher=StarNews|date=July 7, 2012|author=Park Young Woong|accessdate=April 2, 2016}}</ref> She was praised by the director of the show as someone who has \"intelligence\", \"great adaptability\" and the ability to make other cast members get along well.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://star.mt.co.kr/view/stview.php?no=2011121610380060767&amp;type=1&amp;outlink=1 |script-title=ko:'\uccad\ubd882'CP \"\uc2dc\uccad\uc790\uc758\uacac \uc218\uc6a9..\uc2dc\uc98c1\uacfc \ube44\uc2b7\ud574\uc9c8 \uac83\"|date=December 16, 2011|publisher=StarNews|accessdate=April 2, 2016|language=korean}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2012, stepping into the field of [[voice-over]] for the first time, she was featured in the Korean-dubbed version of animated film ''[[The Outback (2012 film)|The Outback]]''. She voiced a koala character named Miranda. Sunny found the recording process to be initially difficult, stating that because Miranda was such a \"charismatic\" and \"strong\" character, it was hard to express \"with just [her] voice\" as it would have been \"a different story if [she] was showing the actions\". With the help of the director, however, she was able to finally \"grasp the character\".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cine21.com/news/view/mag_id/68723 |script-title=ko:&lt;\ucf54\uc54c\ub77c \ud0a4\ub4dc: \uc601\uc6c5\uc758 \ud0c4\uc0dd>\uc5d0 \ubaa9\uc18c\ub9ac \ucd9c\uc5f0\ud55c \ud0dc\ubbfc\uacfc \uc368\ub2c8|publisher=Cine21.com|date=January 10, 2012|accessdate=April 2, 2016|language=korean}}</ref> In March 2012, Sunny became a host for [[SBS MTV]]'s television program ''Music Island''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://etv.sbs.co.kr/news/news_content.jsp?article_id=E10000501574 |script-title=ko:'\ub2e8\ub3c5 MC' \uc368\ub2c8, \"\uc720\ud76c\uc5f4 \uc120\ubc30\uac00 \ub864 \ubaa8\ub378\"|date=March 13, 2012|publisher=[[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]]|accessdate=April 3, 2016|language=korean}}</ref> During the year, she also recorded two duets\u2014the first song is titled \"I Love You, I Love You\", with [[Brown Eyed Girls]]' member [[Miryo]] while the other one is titled \"It's Me\", with [[f(x) (band)|f(x)]]'s [[Luna (singer)|Luna]] for the SBS's drama [[To The Beautiful You]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.segye.com/content/html/2012/02/01/20120201001206.html |script-title=ko:\ubbf8\ub8cc, \uccab \uc194\ub85c \"\ub098\ub974\uc0e4-'\uc18c\uc2dc' \uc368\ub2c8 \ud53c\ucc98\ub9c1 \uad00\uc2ec\"|date=February 1, 2012|accessdate=April 2, 2016|publisher=Segye.com|language=Korean}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=038&aid=0002291206 |script-title=ko:'\uc544\uadf8\ub300' OST PART2, \uc18c\ub140\uc2dc\ub300 \uc368\ub2c8-\uc5d0\ud504\uc5d1\uc2a4 \ub8e8\ub098-\uc0e4\uc774\ub2c8 \uc628\uc720 \ucc38\uc5ec|date=August 22, 2012|accessdate=April 2, 2016|publisher=[[Hankook Ilbo]]|language=Korean}}</ref> The songs debuted at number 56 and 25 on the [[Gaon Digital Chart]] and at number 51 and 16 on [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'s K-pop Hot 100 chart, respectively.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=ALL&targetTime=06&hitYear=2012&termGbn=week|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160312164328/http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?serviceGbn=ALL&termGbn=week&hitYear=2012&targetTime=06&nationGbn=T|publisher=Gaon Digital Chart (Korea Music Content Industry Association)|title=Gaon Digital Chart: January 29\u2014February 4, 2012|archivedate=March 12, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=ALL&targetTime=35&hitYear=2012&termGbn=week|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304193034/http://www.gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=ALL&targetTime=35&hitYear=2012&termGbn=week|date=March 4, 2016|publisher=Gaon Digital Chart (Korea Music Content Industry Association)|title=Gaon Digital Chart: August 19\u201425, 2012|archivedate=March 4, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/biz/search/charts?f%5B0%5D%3Dts_chart_artistname:Miryo%26f%5B1%5D%3Dss_bb_type:chart_item%26type%3D2%26artist%3DMiryo |title=Billboard Chart Search: Miryo |publisher=Billboard |access-date=April 2, 2016 |archive-date=April 2, 2016 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6gTdF5eBf?url=http://www.billboard.com/biz/search/charts?f%5b0%5d=ts_chart_artistname:Miryo&f%5b1%5d=ss_bb_type:chart_item&type=2&artist=Miryo  }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/k-pop-hot-100/2012-09-08|title=Billboard: Korea K-pop Hot 100 - September 8, 2012|publisher=[[Korea K-Pop Hot 100]]|accessdate=April 2, 2016}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Sunny at Style Icon Asia 2016 02.jpg|alt=|right|thumb|Sunny at Style Icon Asia on March 15, 2016.]]\n\nDuring 2012-2013, Sunny was cast in her first musical, ''[[Catch Me If You Can (musical)|Catch Me If You Can]]'', based on the true story and life of a con man named [[Frank Abagnale]]. The story was turned famous by the 2002 movie [[Catch Me If You Can|of the same name]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hancinema.net/musical-catch-me-if-you-can-6-casts-for-one-role-49037.html|title=Musical \"Catch Me If You Can\", 6 casts for one role|publisher=[[Hancinema]]|date=October 25, 2012|accessdate=August 6, 2015}}</ref> She played a character named Brenda, who is the girlfriend of the male lead. Her performance received favorable reviews. Shin Yeong-seon from [[The Chosun Ilbo]] noted on Sunny's ability to understand the character and praised her well-portrayal of Brenda's \"exaggerated cuteness and flippant acting\". Jang Kyungjin of 10asia enjoyed her singing, \"While Sunny wasn't a member in her group who put her vocals forth, she showed her power through Brenda's 'Fly, Fly Away' with her clean, firm voice, showing her potential to the audience.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://media.daum.net/culture/art/view.html?cateid=1021&newsid=20120402031813123&p=chosun&mredirect=false |script-title=ko:'\uce90\uce58\ubbf8'\uc758 \ub2e4\uc12f \uc0c9\uae54 \uacf5\uc5f0(\uc8fc\uc778\uacf5 \ud55c \uba85\uc5d0 \uc5c4\uae30\uc900\u00b7\uae40\uc815\ud6c8\u00b7\ubc15\uad11\ud604\u00b7\uaddc\ud604\u00b7\ud0a4 \uce90\uc2a4\ud305)\u2026 \ub118\uce58\uace0, \ubaa8\uc790\ub77c\uace0|publisher=[[The Chosun Ilbo]]|date=April 2, 2012|accessdate=April 2, 2016|language=korean}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://tenasia.hankyung.com/archives/14303 |script-title=ko:[\ubba4\uc9c0\uceec\uc804\uacfc] Special. \uc544\uc774\ub3cc\uac00\uc218 \ud3b8|work=10asia|publisher=[[Korea Economic Daily]]|date=May 6, 2012|accessdate=April 2, 2016|language=Korean}}</ref> Sunny was nominated for the \"Best New Actress\" at the ''6th Musical Awards''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/themusicalawards/posts/346486088738369|title=The Musical Awards Nomination List|publisher=Facebook|date=May 8, 2012|language=Korean|accessdate=April 2, 2016}}</ref> In June 2013, Sunny released the song \"The 2nd Drawer\" for the [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]]'s drama [[The Queen's Classroom (2013 TV series)|The Queen's Classroom]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=011&aid=0002346582 |script-title=ko:\uc18c\ub140\uc2dc\ub300 \uc368\ub2c8, '\uc5ec\uc655\uc758 \uad50\uc2e4' OST\uc5d0 \ucc38\uc5ec '13\uc77c \uc815\uc624 \uacf5\uac1c'|date=June 13, 2013|publisher=[[Hankook Ilbo]]|language=Korean|accessdate=April 3, 2016}}</ref> It debuted at number 76 on K-pop Top 100 Chart.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/biz/search/charts?f%5B0%5D%3Dts_chart_artistname:Sunny%26f%5B1%5D%3Dss_chart_search_title:%2ADrawer%2A%26f%5B2%5D%3Dss_bb_type:chart_item%26type%3D1%26artist%3DSunny%26title%3DDrawer |title=Billboard Chart Search: Sunny |work=Billboard |publisher=Prometheus Global Media |access-date=April 3, 2016 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6gV32vuIt?url=http://www.billboard.com/biz/search/charts?f%5b0%5d=ts_chart_artistname:Sunny&f%5b1%5d=ss_chart_search_title:*Drawer*&f%5b2%5d=ss_bb_type:chart_item&type=1&artist=Sunny&title=Drawer |archive-date=April 3, 2016  }}</ref> In March 2014, Sunny participated in the Korean-dubbed version of the animated film ''[[Rio 2]]''. She voiced Jewel, a female Spix's macaw. The director noted on her ability to not only deliver the lines, but also successfully expressed other sound effects, like breathing. In an interview, Sunny felt that the most appealing part of dubbing is the ability to go back to her childhood.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.maxmovie.com/movie_info/sha_news_view.asp?menuCode=19&subMenuCode=1&mi_id=MI0100326634&contain&keyword&page=1 |script-title=ko:\uc778\ud130\ubdf0\u2502&lt;\ub9ac\uc6242&gt; \uc368\ub2c8 \"\ub3d9\uc2ec\uc73c\ub85c \ub3cc\uc544\uac00\ub294 \uc5ec\ud589, \uc9c0\ub8e8\ud560 \uc0c8\uac00 \uc5c6\ub2e4\"|date=April 21, 2014|publisher=MaxMovie|accessdate=April 3, 2016|language=Korean}}</ref> In June 2014, Sunny was cast in her second musical, [[Singin' in the Rain (musical)|Singin' in the Rain]], based on the 1952 movie [[Singin' in the Rain|of the same name]]. Sunny played Kathy Selden, an aspiring actress.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20140529000652|title=S.M.'s 'Singing in the Rain' trailer released|date=May 29, 2014|accessdate=April 3, 2016|publisher=[[The Korea Herald]]|author=Ha Ji-won}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://tvdaily.asiae.co.kr/read.php3?aid=1404243623724057016 |script-title=ko:'\uc2f1\uc789\uc778\ub354\ub808\uc778' \uace0\uc804\uc758 \uac10\ub3d9\uacfc \ucc28\ubcc4\ud654\ub41c \uc0ac\ub791 \ub178\ub798 [\ub9ac\ubdf0]|work=TVDaily|publisher=ASia Economic|date=July 2, 2014|accessdate=April 3, 2016|language=Korean}}</ref> In November 2014, her solo song, \"First Kiss\", was released as a part of musician Hwang Sung Je's ''Project Super Hero'' series.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://music.naver.com/album/index.nhn?albumId=465307&trackId=4534756|title=''Hwang Sung Je Project Super Hero'' 3rd Line Up|language=korean|publisher=[[Naver]]|date=November 20, 2014|accessdate=November 25, 2014}}</ref>\n\nBetween 2014-2015, she became a cast member of the SBS's reality show [[Roommate (TV series)|Roommate]]. The show featured a group of celebrities living together, sharing the house as well as household tasks.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://star.mt.co.kr/view/stview.php?no=2014022508011878996&type=1&outlink=1 |script-title=ko:'K\ud31d\uc2a4\ud0c03' \ud6c4\uc18d\ud504\ub85c '\ub8f8\uba54\uc774\ud2b8' \ud655\uc815..4\uc6d420\uc77c \uccab\ubc29|date=February 25, 2014|work=Star Today|language=Korean|accessdate=March 9, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://star.mt.co.kr/foreign/starViewEng.html?no=2014091112104000406|title='Girl's Generation\"s 'Sunny' to join [Roommate] Season 2 as a new cast member|publisher=StarNews|date=September 11, 2014|author=Kim Youngjin|accessdate=April 3, 2016}}</ref> During the same period, Sunny hosted the MBC radio show's ''FM Date''. She contributed her own self-written logo song for the show and also won the \"Rookie Radio DJ Award\" at the year-end [[MBC Entertainment Awards]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://osen.mt.co.kr/article/G1109850057 |script-title=ko:\uc368\ub2c8, \uc9c1\uc811 \uc791\uc0ac\u00b7\uc791\uace1\u00b7\uac00\ucc3d 'FM\ub370\uc774\ud2b8' \ub85c\uace0\uc1a1 \uacf5\uac1c|date=May 12, 2014|accessdate=April 3, 2016|language=Korean|publisher=Osen}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20140506000391|title=Girls' Generation's Sunny to host MBC radio 'FM Date'|author=Ha Ji-won|date=May 6, 2014|accessdate=April 3, 2016|publisher=The Korea Herald}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201511161720219005769_2|title=Sunny shares her thoughts on leaving 'FM Date'|author=Lee Hye-won|date=November 16, 2015|accessdate=April 3, 2016|work=KpopHerald|publisher=The Korea Herald}}</ref><ref name=\"radioaward\">{{cite news|url=http://star.mt.co.kr/view/stview.php?no=2014123018171624842&outlink=2&SVEC|script-title=ko:\uc368\ub2c8, \ub77c\ub514\uc624 \uc2e0\uc778\uc0c1 \uc218\uc0c1\uc18c\uac10 \"\ubbf8\uc548\ud558\uace0 \uac10\uc0ac\ud574\uc694\"|publisher=Star News|language=Korean|date=December 30, 2014|accessdate=May 28, 2015}}</ref> In April 2015, Sunny's voice was featured on indie-band Roof Top House's debut single \"Heart Throbbing\".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201504171754590752781_2|title=Sunny to sing with rookie band|date=April 17, 2015|publisher=The Korea Herald|work=KpopHerald|accessdate=April 3, 2016}}</ref> The song managed to enter Gaon Digital Chart at number 89.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=ALL&targetTime=18&hitYear=2015&termGbn=week|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160402133944/http://www.gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?serviceGbn=ALL&termGbn=week&hitYear=2015&targetTime=18&nationGbn=T|title=Gaon Digital Chart: April 19\u201425, 2015|work=[[Gaon Digital Chart]]|publisher=Music Industry Association of Korea|archivedate=April 2, 2016}}</ref> In August-October 2015, she was a co-host for the short-lived [[JTBC]]'s variety show ''Serial Shopping Family''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201508231352566981802_2|title=SNSD Sunny reveals penchant for toys|publisher=[[The Korea Herald]]|work=KpopHerald|date=August 23, 2015|author=Lim Jeong-yeo}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2016, it was revealed that Sunny would be a celebrity judge in the new show, Vocal War: God's Voice. The purpose of the show is to create a one-on-one vocal battle between veteran singers in Korea and talented amateur vocalists.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.soompi.com/2016/03/15/heo-young-ji-and-girls-generations-sunny-to-appear-on-new-variety-show/|title=Heo Young Ji and Girls' Generation's Sunny to Appear on New Variety Show|date=March 15, 2016|publisher=Soompi|work=Soompi|accessdate=April 6, 2016}}</ref> Starting from June 2016, Sunny joined the main cast of the JTBC variety show ''Cheonhajangsa (\ucc9c\ud558\uc7a5\uc0ac)'', a show featuring various traditional markets.<ref>{{cite news |script-title=ko:[\ub2e8\ub3c5] \uc774\uaddc\ud55c\u00b7\uc815\uc9c4\uc6b4\u00b7\uc368\ub2c8, \uac15\ud638\ub3d9 \u65b0\uc608\ub2a5 '\ucc9c\ud558\uc7a5\uc0ac' \ud569\ub958|url=http://osen.mt.co.kr/article/G1110416390|accessdate=July 20, 2016|publisher=Osen}}</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n{{See also|Girls' Generation discography}}\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"2\"| Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Sales\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Gaon Music Chart|KOR]]<br/><ref>Gaon Digital Chart\n*{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=ALL&targetTime=14&hitYear=2010&termGbn=week |script-title=ko:Your Doll - 2010\ub144 14\uc8fc\ucc28 Digital Chart|work=Gaon Music Chart|publisher=Korea Music Content Industry Association|language=ko}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=ALL&targetTime=06&hitYear=2012&termGbn=week |script-title=ko:I Love You, I Love You - 2012\ub144 06\uc8fc\ucc28 Digital Chart|work=Gaon Music Chart|publisher=Korea Music Content Industry Association|language=ko}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=ALL&targetTime=35&hitYear=2012&termGbn=week |script-title=ko:It's Me - 2012\ub144 35\uc8fc\ucc28 Digital Chart|work=Gaon Music Chart|publisher=Korea Music Content Industry Association|language=ko}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=ALL&targetTime=02&hitYear=2014&termGbn=week |script-title=ko:You Are A Miracle - 2014\ub144 02\uc8fc\ucc28 Digital Chart|work=Gaon Music Chart|publisher=Korea Music Content Industry Association|language=ko}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=ALL&targetTime=18&hitYear=2015&termGbn=week |script-title=ko:Heart Throbbing - 2015\ub144 18\uc8fc\ucc28 Digital Chart|work=